quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  16,15,"He has placed into the earth firm mountains, so it does not shake with you, as well as rivers, and pathways so you may find your way"
  16,16,Also by landmarks and stars do people find their way
  16,17,Can the One Who creates be equal to those who do not? Will you not then be mindful
  16,18,"If you tried to count God’s blessings, you would never be able to number them. Surely God is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  16,19,And God knows what you conceal and what you reveal
  16,20,But those ˹idols˺ they invoke besides God cannot create anything—they themselves are created
  16,21,"They are dead, not alive—not even knowing when their followers will be resurrected"
  16,22,"Your God is ˹only˺ One God. As for those who do not believe in the Hereafter, their hearts are in denial, and they are too proud"
  16,23,"Without a doubt, God knows what they conceal and what they reveal. He certainly does not like those who are too proud"
  16,24,"And when it is said to them, “What has your Lord revealed?” They say, “Ancient fables!”"
  16,25,Let them bear their burdens in full on the Day of Judgment as well as some of the burdens of those they mislead without knowledge. Evil indeed is what they will bear
  16,26,"Indeed, those before them had plotted, but God struck at the ˹very˺ foundation of their structure, so the roof collapsed on top of them, and the torment came upon them from where they did not expect"